C%20the%20%3Cem%3EProthom%20Alo%3C%2Fem%3E%20newspaper%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThree%20other%20employees%20of%20Grameen%20Telecom%20were%20also%20granted%20bail.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20four%20were%20first%20sentenced%20to%20six%20months%20in%20prison%20on%20January%201%20but%20were%20immediately%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fbangladesh-muhammad-yunus-sheikh-hasina-labor-rights-grameen-ef0dc95a9319100885f309cdaa3f4477%5C%22%3Egranted%20bail%20for%2030%20days%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20appeal%20their%20sentence%2C%20the%20Associated%20Press%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Sunday%2C%20the%20court%20also%20accepted%20their%20petitions%20challenging%20the%20verdict%20against%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrameen%20Telecom%20is%20accused%20of%20not%20giving%20some%20employees%20permanent%20status%20despite%20them%20completing%20their%20apprentice%20period%2C%20not%20granting%20annual%20leave%20with%20pay%20to%20workers%2C%20not%20forming%20a%20welfare%20fund%20for%20employees%20and%20not%20distributing%205%25%20of%20its%20dividends%20to%20its%20staff%2C%20the%20reports%20by%20%3Cem%3EProthom%20Alo%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20AP%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYunus%20and%20the%20three%20other%20employees%20have%20denied%20any%20wrongdoing.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAs%20my%20lawyers%20have%20convincingly%20argued%20in%20court%2C%20this%20verdict%20against%20me%20is%20contrary%20to%20all%20legal%20precedent%20and%20logic%2C%E2%80%9D%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-67858016%5C%22%3Ethe%20BBC%20quoted%20Yunus%20as%20saying%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%20statement%20after%20the%20January%201%20verdict.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CI%20call%20for%20the%20Bangladeshi%20people%20to%20speak%20in%20one%20voice%20against%20injustice%20and%20in%20favour%20of%20democracy%20and%20human%20rights%20for%20each%20and%20every%20one%20of%20our%20citizens.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAbdullah%20Al%20Mamun%2C%20Yunus%E2%80%99s%20lawyer%2C%20told%C2%A0%3Cem%3EProthom%20Alo%3C%2Fem%3E%20that%20the%20court%20on%20Sunday%20fixed%20the%20next%20date%20for%20hearing%20in%20the%20case%20to%20March%203.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEighty-three-year-old%20Yunus%2C%20who%20won%20the%20Nobel%20Prize%20in%202006%2C%20is%20credited%20with%20lifting%20millions%20out%20of%20poverty%20through%20his%20microfinancing%20bank%2C%20the%20Grameen%20Bank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20AP%2C%20Yunus%E2%80%99s%20supporters%20say%20he%20is%20being%20targeted%20due%20to%20his%20poor%20relations%20with%20Bangladesh%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%98authoritarian%E2%80%99%20leader%2C%20Prime%20Minister%20Sheikh%20Hasina.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BBC%20reports%20that%20while%20the%20reason%20for%20their%20apparent%20feud%20is%20unclear%2C%20his%20supporters%20have%20said%20Hasina%E2%80%99s%20government%20is%20trying%20to%20discredit%20him%20because%20he%20had%20considered%20starting%20a%20political%20outfit%20to%20rival%20her%20ruling%20Awami%20League.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHasina%E2%80%99s%20government%20has%20denied%20that%20the%20case%20against%20Yunus%20is%20politically%20motivated.%20She%20was%20recently%20re-elected%20in%20an%20election%20that%20the%20opposition%20called%20a%20sham%20and%20boycotted.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706533202000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29163146%2FJunus.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmuhammad-yunus-granted-bail-again-bangladesh%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%2083-year-old%20Nobel%20laureate%20will%20remain%20on%20bail%20until%20the%20hearing%20in%20his%20case%20%E2%80%93%20involving%20alleged%20labour%20law%20violations%20by%20his%20company%20Grameen%20Telecom%20%E2%80%93%20is%20complete.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsouth-asia%2Fmuhammad-yunus-granted-bail-again-bangladesh%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Rukun%20Advani%2C%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20and%20the%20Necessity%20to%20Impress%20Others%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29165016%2FUntitled-design-6-2.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EIt%20is%20not%20often%20that%20an%20author%20and%20his%20editor%20strike%20up%20a%20relationship%20that%20survives%2040%20years%20of%20epistolary%20exchanges%20and%20intellectual%20sparring.%20The%20enduring%20and%20occasionally%20fractious%20friendship%20that%20developed%20between%20the%20historian%20Ramachandra%20Guha%20and%20his%20editor%20Rukun%20Advani%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20the%20literary%20memoir%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Cooking%20of%20Books%3A%20A%20Literary%20Memoir.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAn%20excerpt%20is%20below.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EA%20Stephanian%20he%20was%20distinctly%20ambivalent%20about%20was%20their%20exact%20contemporary%2C%20Shashi%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ETharoor.%20Both%20ranked%20first%20in%20their%20class%20%E2%80%93%20Tharoor%20in%20History%2C%20Advani%20in%20English%20%E2%80%93%20but%20there%20the%20resemblance%20ended.%20Shashi%20was%2C%20even%20in%20college%2C%20very%20much%20a%20public%20man%2C%20debating%2C%20acting%2C%20becoming%20president%20of%20the%20Wodehouse%20Society%20and%20of%20the%20Quiz%20Club%20before%20being%20elected%20president%20of%20the%20College%20Union.%20He%20was%20charming%20and%20outgoing%2C%20but%2C%20from%20the%20start%2C%20ferociously%20ambitious.%20Shashi%20wanted%20to%20make%20a%20mark%20in%20the%20world%2C%20quicker%20and%20more%20dramatically%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethan%20any%20Stephanian%20(or%20perhaps%20any%20Indian)%20before%20him.%20Whereas%20Rukun%20had%20no%20ambition%20to%20become%20well%20known.%20In%20college%2C%20all%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20was%20read%2C%20listen%20to%20music%2C%20and%20have%20one-on-one%20conversations%20with%20friends.%20In%20the%20OUP%2C%20all%20he%20wanted%20to%20do%20was%20edit%20books%3B%20while%20he%20gloried%20in%20the%20success%20of%20his%20authors%2C%20he%20never%20remotely%20wanted%20to%20take%20any%20credit%20for%20this.%20As%20we%20have%20seen%2C%20this%20inwardness%20and%20reclusiveness%20deepened%20even%20further%20when%20he%20retreated%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ERanikhet%20and%20ran%20Permanent%20Black%20from%20there.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20328px)%2085vw%2C%20328px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22328%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1.jpeg%20782w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1-196x300.jpeg%20196w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29164317%2FCooking-of-Books-HR-1-667x1024.jpeg%20667w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694831%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22503%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98The%20Cooking%20of%20Books%2C%E2%80%99%20Ramachandra%20Guha%2C%20Juggernaut%2C%202024.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ERukun%20had%20a%20mixed%20opinion%20of%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20as%20a%20writer%2C%20and%20as%20a%20public%20figure.%20Of%20Tharoor%E2%80%98s%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Great%20Indian%20Novel%3C%2Fem%3E%20he%20once%20wrote%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%5BT%5Dhe%20deliberately%20provocative%20immodesty%20of%20the%20title%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eactually%20has%20less%20to%20with%20the%20author%E2%80%99s%20nearly%20incredible%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eself-esteem%20than%20with%20the%20irreverent%2C%20daring%20and%20heady%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eatmosphere%20of%20the%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%20to%20which%20this%20over-spun%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eallegory%20seems%20completely%20traceable.%20The%20proper%20place%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efor%20this%20novel%20to%20have%20been%20serialized%20was%20%3Cem%3EKooler%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3ETalk%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EStephanian%20rag%20made%20up%20of%20wit%2C%20puns%2C%20good%20humour%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esatire%20and%20irreverence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20that%20same%20essay%2C%20Rukun%20compared%20Tharoor%20unfavourably%20to%20other%20novelists%20from%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s.%20Whereas%20the%20language%20of%20Upamanyu%20Chatterjee%2C%20was%2C%20he%20thought%2C%20%E2%80%98a%20very%20much%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Emore%20refined%20and%20reflective%20version%E2%80%99%20of%20Kooler%20Talk%2C%20both%20%E2%80%98Allan%20Sealy%20and%20Amitav%20Ghosh%20are%20traceable%20to%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%20much%20less%20easily%20and%20much%20more%20obscurely%20than%20Tharoor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eand%20Chatterjee%E2%80%99.%20While%20taking%20something%20from%20their%20old%20college%2C%20these%20more%20gifted%20writers%20had%20outgrown%20its%20milieu%2C%20tackling%20complex%20historical%20and%20moral%20questions%20beyond%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20grasp%20of%20the%20common%20or%20garden%20variety%20of%20Stephanian%20novelist.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20is%20well%20known%2C%20after%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s%2C%20Shashi%20Tharoor%20went%20on%20to%20a%20long%20and%20distinguished%20career%20at%20the%20United%20Nations%2C%20before%20returning%20to%20India%20to%20enter%20politics%20and%20joining%20the%20Congress%20Party.%20He%20became%20a%20member%20of%20Parliament%2C%20then%20a%20Union%20minister%2C%20before%20being%20sacked%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20part%20because%20of%20a%20jokey%20tweet%2C%20and%20in%20part%20because%20he%20seemed%20keener%20in%20involving%20himself%20in%20India%E2%80%99s%20foremost%20cricket%20tournament%2C%20the%20IPL%20(Indian%20Premier%20League)%2C%20than%20in%20discharging%20his%20responsibilities%20as%20a%20minister.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20Tharoor%20was%20asked%20to%20resign%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20Rukun%20wrote%20me%20a%20mail%20combining%20compassion%20with%20sarcasm%2C%20which%20must%20%E2%80%93%20only%20slightly%20redacted%20%E2%80%93%20now%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebe%20made%20public%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20feel%20a%20bit%20sorry%20for%20him.%20So%20much%20ambition%2C%20and%20successful%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eall%20the%20way%20till%20the%20failed%20attempt%20to%20become%20UN%20chief.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EAnd%20now%20the%20first%20big%20political%20victim%20of%20something%20as%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esilly%20as%20a%20Tweet.%20Poetic%20justice%20I%20guess%20for%20former%20editor%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eof%20that%20expanded%20version%20of%20tweeting%2C%20Kooler%20Talk.%20He%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ecompletely%20secular%20and%20personally%20decent%2C%20a%20good%20man%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Efallen%20among%20thieves.%20Since%20he%20has%20literary%20ambition%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eas%20well%2C%20a%20good%20analogy%20seems%20Tharoor%20as%20Macbeth%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ewith%20vaulting%20ambition%20.%20.%20.%20trying%20to%20dethrone%20King%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ELalit%20Duncan%20Modi%20and%20coming%20a%20cropper.%20But%20I%20fear%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esomething%20worse%20is%20going%20to%20befall%20us%20now%3A%20he%20will%20inflict%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehis%20third-rate%20narcissistic%20journalism%20on%20us%20once%20again.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20should%20plead%20with%20Nirmala%20Lakshman%20%5Beditor%20of%20the%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cem%3EHindu%20Sunday%20Magazine%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20where%20Tharoor%20had%20a%20column%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebefore%20he%20joined%20politics%5D%20to%20run%20for%20her%20life%20before%20he%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Estarts%20badgering%20her.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EShashi%20Tharoor%20and%20Rukun%20Advani%20were%20exact%20contemporaries%20at%20St.%20Stephen%E2%80%99s.%20Superficially%2C%20they%20were%20alike%3B%20both%20brilliant%2C%20both%20very%20widely%20read%2C%20each%20far%20removed%20in%20his%20interests%20from%20the%20%E2%80%98sports%20type%E2%80%99%20that%20I%20myself%20was%20in%20college.%20Even%20some%20of%20their%20literary%20tastes%20overlapped%3B%20both%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eadmired%20Wodehouse%20and%20Orwell%2C%20for%20example.%20Yet%20in%20terms%20of%20character%20and%20personality%20no%20two%20Stephanians%20could%20be%20so%20radically%20dissimilar.%20I%20suspect%20most%20readers%20of%20this%20book%20will%20know%20Shashi%20Tharoor%E2%80%99s%20public%20profile.%20To%20show%20how%20Rukun%20Advani%20is%2C%20as%20it%20were%2C%20his%20absolute%20Other%2C%20I%20must%20take%20recourse%20to%20the%20words%20of%20the%20most%20gifted%20of%20all%20Stephanian%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eprose%20stylists%2C%20Mukul%20Kesavan%3A%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%5BRukun%5D%20has%20no%20interest%20in%20impressing%20others.%20This%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Esounds%20impressive%20but%20it%20isn%E2%80%99t%20because%20this%20freedom%20from%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ehuman%20neediness%20isn%E2%80%99t%20down%20to%20modesty%20or%20reticence%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eor%20some%20karmic%20insight%20into%20the%20general%20maya-ness%20of%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ethings.%20It%E2%80%99s%20simpler%20than%20that%2C%20so%20simple%20that%20he%20can%E2%80%99t%20take%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Eany%20credit%20for%20it%3A%20Rukun%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20like%20People.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIt%20explains%20everything%20about%20him.%20This%20is%20why%20he%20lives%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ein%20the%20hills.%20This%20is%20why%20he%20loved%20%5Bhis%20dog%5D%20Biscoot%20without%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ereservation%3A%20he%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20human.%20He%20loves%20Beethoven%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3Ebecause%20he%E2%80%99s%20dead%20and%20his%20genius%20can%20be%20electro