3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Felie-wiesel-survived-auschwitz-to-give-us-a-vivid-glimpse-of-the-kingdom-of-night-62024%5C%22%3EAuschwitz%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20Nazi-occupied%20Poland%2C%20was%20the%20only%20camp%20where%20numbers%20were%20tattooed%20on%20those%20inmates%20not%20selected%20for%20immediate%20death.%20In%20replacing%20the%20person%E2%80%99s%20name%2C%20this%20number%20has%20become%20the%20visual%20symbol%20of%20the%20crimes%20of%20the%20Nazis.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20draws%20meaning%20from%20her%20tattoo%20in%20that%20it%20signifies%20her%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20history%20and%20her%20own%20identity%20as%20a%20descendant%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors.%20To%20her%20mind%2C%20replicating%20this%20number%20was%20a%20means%20of%20taking%20her%20grandmother%2C%20as%20a%20person%2C%20and%20her%20legacy%20forward.%20As%20a%20gesture%20and%20an%20indelible%20mark%20she%20carries%20with%20her%2C%20she%20says%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20number%20is%20my%20grandma.%20It%E2%80%99s%20my%20past%2C%20my%20roots%2C%20my%20story.%20It%E2%80%99s%20who%20I%20am.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20potent%20gesture%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Fpdf%2F10.1177%2F07255136211042453%5C%22%3EMy%20research%3C%2Fa%3E%20delves%20into%20the%20stories%20of%20those%20descendants%20who%2C%20like%20Cohen%2C%20have%20chosen%20to%20replicate%20a%20parent%20or%20a%20grandparent%E2%80%99s%20tattoo%20on%20their%20own%20body.%20Of%20the%2016%20people%20I%20have%20spoken%20with%2C%2013%20are%20from%20Israel%20and%20three%20from%20the%20US.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20number%20of%20remaining%20survivors%20of%20the%20Nazi%20concentration%20camps%20grows%20ever%20smaller%20and%20the%20Holocaust%20passes%20out%20of%20living%20memory%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2F10.1177%2F07255136211042453%5C%22%3Ereplicating%20an%20Auschwitz%20tattoo%3C%2Fa%3E%20becomes%20an%20ever%20more%20potent%20gesture%20about%20embodied%20memorialisation%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20familial%20ties%20and%20love.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20people%20I%20have%20spoken%20with%20have%20relayed%20complex%20and%20varied%20decision-making%20processes%20behind%20this%20potent%20gesture.%20Some%20waited%20until%20their%20survivor%20parent%20or%20grandparent%20had%20died.%20Some%20got%20the%20tattoo%20without%20seeking%20approval.%20Others%20discussed%20doing%20so%20with%20their%20relative%2C%20beforehand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20in%20a%20black%20shirt%20and%20jeans%20holds%20out%20a%20framed%20photograph.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D389%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D389%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D389%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D489%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D489%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570119%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-27-q3ao2u.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D489%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22389%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EOrly%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20with%20a%20photograph%20of%20her%20maternal%20grandparents.%20Photo%3A%20John%20Jeffay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20replica%20tattoos%20they%20have%20each%20opted%20for%20vary%20in%20terms%20of%20font%2C%20colour%20and%20placement.%20Some%20have%20chosen%20to%20replicate%20exactly%20what%20the%20original%20looked%20like%20and%20where%20it%20was%20placed.%20Others%20have%20chosen%20to%20alter%20the%20designs%20in%20detail%20and%20colour%2C%20or%20to%20place%20it%20on%20a%20different%20part%20of%20their%20body.%20Each%20decision%20crafts%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20new%20tattoo.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20I%20met%20with%20Orly%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20on%20Zoom.%20She%20had%20chosen%20to%20have%20her%20maternal%20grandfather%20Samuel%20Kestenbaum%E2%80%99s%20number%20tattooed%20on%20her%20arm%2C%20but%20it%20was%20also%20for%20her%20maternal%20grandmother%2C%20Agi%20Kestenbaum.%20She%20had%20been%20in%20Auschwitz%20too%2C%20but%20was%20not%20tattooed%20because%20she%20was%20not%20expected%20to%20live.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELike%20Cohen%2C%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20remember%20a%20specific%20time%20when%20she%20first%20noticed%20her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20number%2C%20but%20the%20stories%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20were%20a%20part%20of%20her%20life%20from%20childhood.%20She%20says%20her%20mother%2C%20who%20died%20eight%20years%20before%20we%20spoke%2C%20used%20to%20talk%20a%20lot%20about%20the%20Holocaust.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20knew%20everything%2C%E2%80%9D%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAll%20four%20of%20her%20grandparents%20had%20survived%20the%20Holocaust.%20Her%20paternal%20grandparents%20died%20when%20she%20was%20in%20her%20late%20teens%20and%20even%20now%2C%20she%20says%2C%20her%20father%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20talk%20about%20what%20they%20experienced.%20She%20says%20that%20when%20she%20asks%20her%20father%20questions%2C%20he%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20know%20the%20answers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeintraub%20Gilad%20remains%20very%20close%20to%20her%20grandmother%2C%20who%20is%2095%20years%20old.%20The%20tattoo%20gives%20her%20the%20chance%20to%20continue%20what%20her%20mother%20used%20to%20do%20and%20talk%20about%20the%20Holocaust.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20starts%20the%20conversation%20and%20that%E2%80%99s%20the%20purpose%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9Cthat%E2%80%99s%20the%20thing%20that%20my%20grandmother%20is%20so%20happy%20about.%20She%20knows%20that%20after%20she%E2%80%99s%20gone%2C%20that%20I%20will%20talk.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20tattoo%20itself%20features%20her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20number%20in%20a%20nest%20of%20leafy%20green%20vines.%20From%20different%20vines%20emerge%20letters%2C%20the%20initials%20of%20the%20names%20of%20Weintraub%20Gilad%E2%80%99s%20husband%20and%20her%20children.%20But%20the%20resulting%20composition%20is%20as%20much%20about%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%20history%20as%20it%20is%20about%20their%20collective%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20choice%20of%20green%20vines%20and%20leaves%20came%20from%20her%20love%20of%20nature.%20Her%20grandfather%E2%80%99s%20number%20was%20on%20his%20left%20arm%2C%20but%20Weintraub%20Gilad%20placed%20her%20own%20tattoo%20on%20her%20right%20arm.%20She%20says%20she%20wanted%20%E2%80%9Cto%20do%20it%20the%20same%20but%20different%E2%80%9D.%20One%20reason%20for%20choosing%20the%20right%20arm%20was%20because%20she%20did%20not%20want%20to%20see%20the%20number%20%E2%80%9Con%20the%20side%20of%20the%20heart%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20same%20summer%2C%20I%20spoke%20with%20Yair%20Ron%20(Reisz)%2C%20also%20on%20Zoom.%20He%20grew%20up%20in%20Israel%2C%20on%20a%20kibbutz%20founded%20by%20Holocaust%20survivors.%20%E2%80%9CIt%20was%20a%20very%20small%20community%20of%20people%20with%20same%20idea%20of%20communism%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20of%20them%20were%20Holocaust%20survivors%2C%20so%20all%20of%20them%20have%20numbers.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGrowing%20up%2C%20no%20one%20on%20the%20kibbutz%20had%20grandparents%20or%20spoke%20about%20their%20suffering.%20Ron%E2%80%99s%20father%2C%20Jakub%20Reisz%20%E2%80%93%20whom%20everyone%20knew%20as%20Yakshi%20%E2%80%93%20said%20nothing%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20and%2C%20like%20many%20children%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors%2C%20Ron%20and%20his%20sister%20knew%20not%20to%20ask.%20Yakshi%20would%20talk%20about%20helping%20people%20escape%20from%20Slovakia%20to%20Hungary%20%E2%80%93%20but%20he%20never%20said%20a%20word%20about%20what%20he%20had%20experienced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20impossible%20to%20have%20a%20conversation%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20with%20my%20father.%20We%20were%20afraid%20to%20ask%20and%20afraid%20to%20hear.%20Maybe%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20hear.%20And%20he%20told%20us%20that%20he%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20tell%2C%20so%20we%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20exchange%20any%20information%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20whatsoever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERon%20first%20noticed%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20number%20as%20a%20child.%20Just%20as%20it%20was%20normal%20not%20to%20talk%20about%20things%20%E2%80%93%20about%20families%2C%20generations%2C%20loss%20%E2%80%93%20it%20was%20also%20normal%20to%20him%20and%20his%20peers%20that%20adults%20had%20numbers%20on%20their%20bodies.%20Until%20he%20started%20venturing%20out%20into%20the%20local%20town%20as%20a%20teenager%2C%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20really%20meet%20people%20from%20outside%20of%20the%20kibbutz%20%E2%80%93%20adults%2C%20that%20is%2C%20who%20didn%E2%80%99t%20have%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIt%20seemed%20very%20natural%20to%20us%20that%20adults%20had%20numbers%20so%20we%20didn%E2%80%99t%20pay%20very%20much%20attention%20to%20this.%20We%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20other%20adults%20or%20people%20without%20numbers.%20The%20kibbutz%20was%20far%20away%20in%20the%20mountain%2C%20it%20was%20very%20isolated.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20man%20in%20a%20uniform%20holds%20up%20his%20arm.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D400%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570699%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240122-27-mssuh2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D503%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22400%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EYair%20Ron%20bears%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20number%20on%20his%20arm.%20Photo%3A%20John%20Jeffay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20only%20after%20Yakshi%E2%80%99s%20death%20that%20Ron%20started%20to%20piece%20together%20his%20story.%20Coming%20across%20a%20letter%20and%20diary%20that%20a%20friend%20of%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20had%20written%2C%20Ron%20discovered%20that%20both%20men%20had%20been%20deported%20from%20Slovakia%20to%20Auschwitz.%20They%20had%20then%20been%20taken%20to%20Nazi-run%20work%20camps%2C%20from%20where%20they%20were%20eventually%20liberated.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20their%20release%2C%20they%20started%20their%20journey%20back%20to%20Slovakia%2C%20via%20Prague.%20To%20pass%20through%20the%20British%20military%20area%20without%20being%20detained%2C%20identification%20was%20required.%20Neither%20man%20had%20any%2C%20so%20they%20tattooed%20what%20looked%20like%20Auschwitz%20numbers%20on%20their%20left%20arms.%20Ron%20shared%20what%20he%20had%20learned%20with%20his%20family.%20They%20were%20very%20proud%20of%20Yakshi%2C%20he%20says%2C%20praising%20his%20%E2%80%9Ccreativity%20and%20thinking%20out%20of%20the%20box%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERon%20first%20thought%20about%20getting%20Yakshi%E2%80%99s%20number%20tattooed%20on%20his%20own%20body%20when%20he%20was%20around%2050%20years%20old%2C%20at%20the%20turn%20of%20the%20millennium.%20He%20discussed%20it%20with%20his%20father%20who%2C%20like%20most%20Holocaust%20survivors%2C%20was%20strongly%20opposed%20to%20the%20idea%20at%20first.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20says%20his%20relationship%20with%20his%20father%20was%20not%20an%20easy%20one.%20There%20were%20barriers%20between%20them.%20Ron%20ascribed%20these%2C%20in%20part%2C%20to%20Yakshi%E2%80%99s%20experiences%20of%20the%20Holocaust%20and%20the%20trauma%20he%20lived%20with.%20But%20it%20was%20more%20complex%20than%20that.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKibbutzim%20in%20the%201950s%20and%201960s%2C%20like%20the%20one%20Ron%20grew%20up%20on%2C%20were%20often%20organised%20around%20collective-socialist%20principles.%20Until%20the%201980s%2C%20children%20were%20raised%20separately%20from%20their%20parents%20and%20slept%20in%20a%20communal%20children%E2%80%99s%20house.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov%2Fpmc%2Farticles%2FPMC7753919%2F%5C%22%3EResearch%20has%20shown%3C%2Fa%3E%20variable%20attachment%20responses%20among%20those%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20this%20way%20%E2%80%93%20although%20it%20found%20little%20variation%20in%20attachment%20to%20fathers%2C%20compared%20with%20those%20who%20grew%20up%20in%20family%20homes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERon%20wonders%2C%20however%2C%20whether%20the%20fact%20that%20he%20and%20Yakshi%20did%20not%20enjoy%20a%20%E2%80%9Cnormal%E2%80%9D%20relationship%20is%20in%20some%20part%20due%20to%20growing%20up%20this%20way.%20Although%20he%20saw%20his%20father%20as%20a%20good%20man%2C%20the%20distance%20between%20them%20meant%20they%20could%20not%20speak%20about%2C%20as%20he%20puts%20it%2C%20%E2%80%9Creal%20feelings%20and%20thoughts%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20the%20number%20on%20his%20own%20body%2C%20Ron%20says%2C%20allowed%20him%20to%20reflect%20on%20what%20it%20is%20to%20live%20%E2%80%9Clike%20a%20numbered%20person%E2%80%9D.%20As%20survivors%20die%20out%2C%20he%20dwells%20on%20the%20thought%20that%20soon%20there%20will%20be%20no%20numbered%20people.%20This%2C%20to%20his%20mind%2C%20makes%20the%20number%20an%20important%20thing%20to%20keep%20%E2%80%93%20a%20tool%20for%20keeping%20the%20memory%20alive.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ETattooing%20in%20Auschwitz%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESerial%20number%20tattoos%20with%20symbols%2C%20shapes%20or%20letters%20were%20first%20introduced%20for%20prisoners%20in%20the%20Auschwitz%20concentration%20camp%20complex%20in%20October%201941.%20More%20than%20400%2C000%20people%20would%20be%20tattooed%20there.%20The%20exceptions%20were%20ethnic%20Germans%2C%20Austrians%2C%20police%20prisoners%20and%20Polish%20prisoners%20deported%20from%20Warsaw%20during%20the%201944%20uprising%20%E2%80%93%20plus%20Jewish%20prisoners%20held%20for%20a%20short%20time%20while%20waiting%20to%20be%20moved%20to%20other%20camps.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrior%20to%20tattoos%2C%20identification%20numbers%20had%20been%20sewn%20on%20to%20the%20prison%20uniforms.%20Soviet%20prisoners%20of%20war%20were%20the%20first%20group%20to%20be%20tattooed%20after%20larger%20numbers%20started%20to%20die%20and%20the%20other%20prisoners%20took%20the%20deceased%E2%80%99s%20clothing%2C%20making%20it%20impossible%20to%20keep%20accurate%20records.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInitially%2C%20the%20tattoos%20were%20placed%20on%20the%20left%20side%20of%20each%20prisoner%E2%80%99s%20chest.%20Those%20who%20did%20the%20tattooing%20used%20a%20metal%20stamp%20with%20changeable%20plates%20fitted%20with%20needles%20that%20formed%20numbers%2C%20then%20rubbed%20blue%20ink%20into%20the%20bleeding%20holes.%20This%20technique%20enabled%20guards%20and%20prisoners%20to%20tattoo%20the%20number%20on%20a%20prisoner%E2%80%99s%20body%20in%20a%20single%20action.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20spring%20of%201942%2C%20all%20incoming%20Jewish%20prisoners%20selected%20for%20forced%20labour%2C%20rather%20than%20immediate%20death%2C%20were%20tattooed.%20In%20place%20of%20the%20metal%20plate%2C%20the%20tattooists%20now%20used%20a%20single%20needle%20to%20puncture%20the%20number%20into%20the%20prisoner%E2%80%99s%20skin%20by%20hand%2C%20then%20rubbed%20in%20the%20ink.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20numbers%20were%20tattooed%20on%20the%20prisoners%E2%80%99%20left%20forearms.%20Shapes%20and%20letters%20were%20sometimes%20also%20used%20to%20differentiate%20between%20groups%20of%20prisoners.%20Some%20Jewish%20prisoners%20had%20a%20triangle%20tattooed%20under%20their%20number.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fthe-genocide-of-the-roma-and-how-commemoration-of-this-forgotten-holocaust-is-shifting-92771%5C%22%3ERoma%20and%20Sinti%20prisoners%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20the%20letter%20Z%20appended%20to%20their%20number%2C%20the%20first%20letter%20of%20the%20(pejorative)%20German%20word%20%3Cem%3EZigeuner%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20used%20at%20the%20time%20for%20these%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20Hungarian%20Jews%20arriving%20in%20increasing%20numbers%2C%20new%20sequences%20of%20digits%20were%20introduced%20in%20May%201944.%20These%20began%20with%20the%20number%201%20and%20were%20prefaced%20first%20by%20the%20letter%20A%3B%20then%2C%20when%20more%20were%20needed%2C%20B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20her%202001%20autobiographical%20book%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbooks.google.co.uk%2Fbooks%2Fabout%2FStill_Alive.html%3Fid%3DNX5Fj8rLqkIC%26redir_esc%3Dy%5C%22%3EStill%20Alive%3A%20A%20Holocaust%20Girlhood%20Remembered%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20German%20studies%20scholar%20and%20Holocaust%20survivor%20Ruth%20Kl%C3%BCger%20describes%20the%20experience%20of%20getting%20forcibly%20tattooed%20in%20Auschwitz%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3E%5BAfter%20selection%5D%2C%20we%20got%20our%20ID%20numbers%20tattooed%20on%20our%20left%20arms.%20A%20few%20female%20prisoners%20had%20been%20installed%20outside%20the%20building%20at%20a%20table%20with%20the%20necessary%20equipment%20and%20we%20stood%20in%20line%2C%20waiting%20our%20turn.%20The%20women%20knew%20their%20job%2C%20they%20were%20very%20fast.%20At%20first%20it%20looked%20as%20if%20the%20black%20ink%20would%20easily%20wash%20off%2C%20and%20indeed%2C%20water%20took%20most%20of%20it%20away%2C%20but%20then%20the%20fine%20points%20of%20the%20number%20remained%3A%20A-3537.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKl%C3%BCger%20speaks%20about%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20victims%E2%80%99%20skin%E2%80%9D%20saving%20the%20Nazis%20from%20having%20to%20%E2%80%9Cproduce%20dog%20tags%E2%80%9D.%20This%20underlines%20how%20dehumanising%20this%20Nazi%20practice%20of%20tattooing%20numbers%20on%20inmates%20was.%20As%20the%20Italian%20writer%20and%20Holocaust%20survivor%20Primo%20Levi%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fjournals.sagepub.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1177%2F07255136211042453%5C%22%3Eputs%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20his%201986%20book%2C%20The%20Drowned%20and%20the%20Saved%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EIts%20symbolic%20meaning%20was%20clear%20to%20everyone%3A%20this%20is%20an%20indelible%20mark%2C%20you%20will%20never%20leave%20here%3B%20this%20is%20the%20mark%20with%20which%20slaves%20are%20branded%20and%20cattle%20sent%20to%20slaughter%2C%20and%20that%20is%20what%20you%20have%20become.%20You%20no%20longer%20have%20a%20name%3B%20this%20is%20your%20new%20name.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAn%20embodied%20public%20memorial%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Auschwitz%20number%20has%20marked%20out%20those%20who%20survived%20by%20making%20them%20ever%20recognisable%20to%20others.%20It%20is%20this%20recognition%20that%20mattered%20so%20much%20to%20Rony%20Cohen%20in%20getting%20her%20own%20tattoo%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI%20was%20proud%20to%20take%20my%20grandmother%20with%20me.%20To%20take%20her%20childhood%2C%20her%20missing%20her%20parents%20%E2%80%93%20those%20moments%20are%20in%20this%20number.%20Whenever%20someone%20sees%20it%2C%20they%20know%20this%20is%20Auschwitz.%20I%20want%20it%20to%20be%20noticed%20and%20understandable.%20No%20one%20should%20doubt%20what%20it%20is.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%E2%80%99s%20grandmother%20and%20great%20uncle%20were%20of%20the%20cohort%20of%20siblings%20that%20have%20become%20known%20as%20%E2%80%9CMengele%20twins%E2%80%9D.%20The%20Nazi%20physician%20Josef%20Mengele%20had%20an%20interest%20in%20racial%20genetics.%20He%20first%20experimented%20on%20Roma%20and%20Sinti%20twins%20in%20what%20was%20known%20as%20the%20%E2%80%9CGypsy%20camp%E2%80%9D%20in%20Auschwitz-Birkenau%20%E2%80%93%20then%20on%20Jewish%20prisoners%20who%20he%20picked%20from%20the%20Theresienstadt%20camp-ghetto%20in%20Terez%C3%ADn%2C%20in%20the%20Protectorate%20of%20Bohemia%20and%20Moravia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20May%201944%2C%20subjects%20for%20Mengele%E2%80%99s%20experiments%20were%20also%20picked%20from%20the%20unloading%20ramps%20at%20Auschwitz.%20Cohen%20recalled%20the%20story%20her%20grandmother%20had%20told%20her%2C%20about%20how%20she%20arrived%20in%20Auschwitz%20with%20her%20twin%20brother%2C%20aged%20eight%2C%20and%20her%20mother%20and%20aunts%20and%20all%20the%20other%20children%20of%20the%20family%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20saw%20the%20smoke%20from%20the%20crematorium.%20The%20family%20was%20walking%20and%20someone%20was%20saying%3A%20%E2%80%98Twins%2C%20twins%2C%20twins%20%E2%80%93%20where%E2%80%99s%20twins%3F%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInstead%20of%20hiding%20them%2C%20her%20mother%20said%20to%20her%20aunts%2C%20%E2%80%9CLet%E2%80%99s%20give%20them%20the%20twins%E2%80%9D.%20Her%20aunts%20thought%20she%20was%20crazy%20for%20suggesting%20that%20%E2%80%93%20but%20her%20mother%20thought%20she%20was%20saving%20her%20children.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20going%20to%20save%20your%20life%20now%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20told%20her%20children.%20%E2%80%9CGive%20mummy%20a%20hug%20and%20you%E2%80%99re%20leaving%20now.%E2%80%9D%20This%20was%20the%20last%20moment%20Cohen%E2%80%99s%20grandmother%20could%20remember%20being%20with%20her%20mother.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaving%20made%20it%20through%20selection%20and%20been%20forcibly%20tattooed%2C%20twins%20were%20sometimes%20given%20additional%20food%20which%20helped%20keep%20them%20alive.%20First-hand%20accounts%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcollections.ushmm.org%2Fsearch%2Fcatalog%2Fbib4007%5C%22%3Edescribe%3C%2Fa%3E%20how%20Mengele%20gave%20his%20victims%20chocolate%20before%20carrying%20out%20the%20most%20horrific%20experiments.%20He%20sewed%20twins%E2%80%99%20veins%20together%2C%20injected%20chemicals%20into%20testicles%20and%20spines%2C%20and%20inserted%20large%20needles%20into%20skulls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%201994%20book%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcollections.ushmm.org%2Fsearch%2Fcatalog%2Fbib4007%5C%22%3EAnatomy%20of%20the%20Auschwitz%20Death%20Camp%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20chapter%20by%20historian%20Helena%20Kubica%20recounts%20the%20testimony%20of%20one%20man%2C%20Moshe%20Ofer%2C%20who%20was%20imprisoned%20with%20his%20twin%20brother.%20His%20testimony%20was%20collected%20by%20the%20Jerusalem%20tribunal%20that%20tried%20Mengele%20in%20absentia%20in%201985.%20Mengele%20killed%20Ofer%E2%80%99s%20brother%20with%20his%20experiments.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfer%20describes%20how%2C%20after%20the%20experiments%2C%20the%20physician%20would%20bring%20gifts.%20The%20horror%20of%20that%20had%20never%20left%20him.%20%E2%80%9CEven%20today%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20can%20see%20him%20entering%20through%20the%20door%20and%20I%20am%20paralysed%20with%20fear.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%E2%80%99s%20grandmother%20similarly%20recalled%20Mengele%20bringing%20food%20for%20the%20twins.%20It%20saved%20them%20physically%2C%20she%20said%2C%20but%20the%20psychological%20damage%20was%20immeasurable.%20As%20Cohen%20puts%20it%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20grandmother%2C%20since%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20she%20has%20a%20sleeping%20disorder.%20In%20her%20dreams%2C%20her%20parents%20come%20and%20all%20the%20horror%20comes.%20She%20always%20tells%20me%3A%20%E2%80%98I%20can%E2%80%99t%20forgive%20myself%20that%20I%20remember%20Mengele%E2%80%99s%20face%20but%20I%20can%E2%80%99t%20remember%20my%20parents%E2%80%99%20faces.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHer%20brother%20%E2%80%93%20Cohen%E2%80%99s%20great%20uncle%20%E2%80%93%20had%20his%20tattoo%20removed%20after%20saving%20enough%20money.%20Her%20grandmother%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20still%20bears%20it%20on%20her%20left%20arm.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20child%2C%20Cohen%20would%20ask%20questions.%20Sometimes%20her%20grandmother%20would%20make%20out%20that%20it%20was%20nothing.%20Sometimes%20she%E2%80%99d%20say%20she%20would%20tell%20her%20when%20she%20was%20older.%20Cohen%20describes%20herself%20as%20stubborn%20%E2%80%93%20she%20just%20kept%20asking.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20she%20was%2012%20or%2013%2C%20for%20a%20school%20project%20on%20roots%2C%20she%20decided%20to%20do%20a%20video%20on%20her%20family%E2%80%99s%20history.%20Cohen%20interviewed%20both%20her%20maternal%20grandparents.%20Her%20grandfather%20she%20describes%20as%20%E2%80%9Ctough%E2%80%9D%2C%20with%20%E2%80%9Call%20the%20characteristics%20of%20a%20typical%20survivor%E2%80%9D.%20He%20was%20keen%20that%20Cohen%20pass%20on%20all%20the%20information%20to%20her%20mother%20because%2C%20he%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CYour%20mum%20never%20asked.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20shared%20everything%20with%20her%20mother%20and%20her%20uncle%20%E2%80%93%20and%20it%20finally%20removed%20the%20elephant%20from%20the%20room.%20It%20made%20talking%20about%20the%20Holocaust%20possible.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%2017%2C%20like%20so%20many%20Israelis%2C%20Cohen%20went%20on%20a%20high-school%20visit%20to%20Poland%2C%20to%20the%20camps%20and%20the%20ghettos.%20Before%20leaving%20on%20this%20trip%2C%20she%20went%20to%20see%20her%20grandfather.%20He%20told%20her%20that%20going%20to%20Auschwitz%20would%20change%20everything%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20you%20stand%20there%20in%20those%20walls%20and%20you%20smell%20the%20death%20smell%20and%20you%20see%20the%20gas%20chamber%2C%20you%20will%20come%20back%20to%20Israel%20and%20you%20will%20tell%20me%3A%20%E2%80%98I%20can%E2%80%99t%20understand.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CI%20can%E2%80%99t%20understand%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20now%20says.%20%E2%80%9CMy%20grandfather%20was%20so%20right.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20Holocaust%20memorialisation%20has%20changed%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Auschwitz%20number%20tattoo%20was%20not%20always%20revered.%20After%20the%20second%20world%20war%2C%20survivors%20were%20often%20stigmatised.%20Public%20commemorations%20celebrated%20resistance%20and%20uprisings.%20The%20victims%20and%20survivors%2C%20by%20contrast%2C%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.tandfonline.com%2Fdoi%2Fabs%2F10.1080%2F02757206.2020.1726907%5C%22%3Eportrayed%20as%20weak%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20early%20stigmatisation%20would%20follow%20some%20survivors%20throughout%20their%20lives%2C%20even%20when%20public%20perception%20started%20to%20shift.%20Some%2C%20like%20Cohen%E2%80%99s%20great%20uncle%2C%20had%20their%20number%20removed.%20Others%20covered%20it%20up%20with%20long%20sleeves.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20the%20early%201960s%2C%20as%20French%20historian%20Annette%20Wieviorka%20shows%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cornellpress.cornell.edu%2Fbook%2F9780801443312%2Fthe-era-of-the-witness%2F%23bookTabs%3D1%5C%22%3EThe%20Era%20of%20The%20Witness%3C%2Fa%3E%20(2006)%2C%20attitudes%20began%20to%20change%20%E2%80%93%20partly%20due%20to%20the%20testimonies%20heard%20during%20the%20trial%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.yadvashem.org%2Fholocaust%2Feichmann-trial%2Fabout.html%5C%22%3EAdolf%20Eichmann%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201961-62.%20The%20author%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F1963%2F02%2F16%2Feichmann-in-jerusalem-i%5C%22%3EHannah%20Arendt%3C%2Fa%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2Fa-reporter-at-large%2F02%2F23%2Feichmann-in-jerusalem-ii%5C%22%3Ereported%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F1963%2F03%2F02%2Fiii-eichmann-in-jerusalem%5C%22%3Edistrict%20court%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2Fmjn-%3D1963%2F03%2F09%2Feichmann-in-jerusalem-iv%5C%22%3EJerusalem%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.newyorker.com%2Fmagazine%2F1963%2F03%2F16%2Feichmann-in-jerusalem-v%5C%22%3ENew%20Yorker%3C%2Fa%3E%20magazine%2C%20thereby%20giving%20survivor%20voices%20a%20global%20platform.%20The%20trauma%20that%20emerged%20from%20Eichmann%E2%80%99s%20trial%20reframed%20survival%20in%20itself%20as%20something%20heroic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20black%20and%20white%20photograph%20of%20a%20court%20trial.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D504%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D504%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D504%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D634%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D634%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570170%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-23-vfrt3z.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D634%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22504%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EAdolf%20Eichmann%20is%20sentenced%20to%20death%20in%20Jerusalem%20on%20December%2015%201961.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20commons%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20in%201967%2C%20Israel%20responded%20to%20threats%20from%20Egypt%20and%20other%20neighbouring%20states%20with%20an%20offensive%20that%20allowed%20it%20to%20expand%20into%20and%20occupy%20the%20Sinai%20Peninsula%2C%20the%20Gaza%20Strip%2C%20the%20West%20Bank%2C%20East%20Jerusalem%20and%20the%20Golan%20Heights.%20Further%20afield%2C%20the%20conflict%20%E2%80%93%20known%20as%20the%20six-day%20war%20%E2%80%93%20built%20an%20affinity%20between%20Jewish%20communities%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Israel.%20Many%20American%20Jews%20began%20to%20both%20embrace%20their%20European%20roots%20and%20support%20Zionism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWieviorka%E2%80%99s%20book%20highlights%20the%20third%20(and%20ongoing)%20phase%20of%20Holocaust%20memorialisation%20%E2%80%93%20what%20she%20terms%20the%20%E2%80%9Cera%20of%20the%20witness%E2%80%9D%2C%20which%20emerged%20in%20the%201970s.%20People%20started%20collating%20survivor%20testimonies%2C%20photographs%20and%20documentation.%20Through%20visits%20to%20Poland%2C%20to%20the%20camps%20and%20ghettos%2C%20families%20began%20to%20tell%20their%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fnyupress.org%2F9781479839292%2Fthe-holocaust-across-generations%2F%5C%22%3Estories%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20some%2C%20the%20visit%20to%20Poland%20triggered%20the%20idea%20of%20replicating%20the%20Auschwitz%20number%20on%20their%20own%20body.%20In%20the%20summer%20of%202022%2C%20I%20spoke%20with%20Zeev%20Forkosh.%20Now%20aged%2038%2C%20he%20has%20multiple%20tattoos%20%E2%80%93%20but%20the%20idea%20for%20his%20first%20one%20came%20after%20going%20to%20Auschwitz.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20new%20information%20Forkosh%20learned%20during%20that%20trip%2C%20about%20what%20his%20grandmother%20had%20experienced%20there%2C%20sparked%20such%20powerful%20emotions%20that%20he%20decided%20to%20get%20a%20Holocaust%20memorial%20tattoo.%20He%20describes%20the%20large%20Star%20of%20David%20he%20wears%20on%20his%20back%20as%20entwined%20with%20%E2%80%9Cbones%2C%20flesh%20and%20a%20lot%20of%20clothes%2C%20like%20the%20Holocaust%20survivors%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENext%2C%20Forkosh%20decided%20to%20replicate%20his%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20number%20on%20his%20arm%2C%20explaining%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI%20will%20never%20forget%20this%20trip%2C%20so%20it%E2%80%99s%20on%20my%20back%20now.%20But%20after%20a%20few%20years%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20be%20more%20specific%20about%20my%20grandmother.%20I%20told%20the%20tattoo%20artist%20that%20this%20was%20for%20%5Bher%5D.%20I%E2%80%99m%20a%20third%20generation%20of%20a%20Holocaust%20survivor.%20I%20think%20it%E2%80%99s%20the%20most%20beautiful%20tattoo%20ever.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20of%20this%20number%20in%20terms%20of%20beauty%20underscores%20how%20reproducing%20the%20tattoo%20gives%20it%20new%20meaning.%20It%20is%20a%20gesture%20that%2C%20for%20Forkosh%2C%20turns%20the%20visual%20symbol%20of%20a%20genocide%20into%20a%20symbol%20of%20love%20and%20legacy%2C%20of%20commemoration%20and%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20close-up%20of%20an%20arm%20tattoo.%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22600%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D302%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D302%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D302%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D379%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D379%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F570157%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20240118-15-na6vez.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D379%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22302%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EYair%20Ron%20replicated%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20number%20exactly.%20Photo%3A%20John%20Jeffay%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20marks%20a%20radical%20shift%20from%20survivors%E2%80%99%20own%20relationships%20with%20the%20number.%20They%20had%20no%20choice%20in%20the%20matter%3A%20the%20tattoo%20was%20forcibly%20placed%20on%20their%20bodies.%20For%20some%20whose%20descendants%20suggested%20replicating%20it%2C%20the%20answer%20has%20always%20been%20a%20categorical%20%E2%80%9Cno%E2%80%9D.%20Yair%20Ron%20discussed%20the%20idea%20with%20his%20father%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%3E%3Cp%3EI%20tried%20to%20talk%20to%20him%20about%20the%20idea%20that%20I%20had%20to%20get%20the%20tattoo.%20He%20did%20not%20agree.%20%E2%80%98Why%3F%E2%80%99%20he%20asked.%20%E2%80%98You%20don%E2%80%99t%20need%20to%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20good.%20Let%E2%80%99s%20forget%20everything.%E2%80%99%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERon%20kept%20trying%3A%20%E2%80%9CIt%20took%20a%20few%20years%20for%20us%20to%20talk%20about%20it.%20And%20then%20he%20agreed%20for%20me%20to%20do%20it.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20gave%20the%20tattoo%20artist%20a%20photo%20of%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20number.%20He%20wanted%20to%20replicate%20it%20as%20closely%20as%20possible.%20He%20wanted%20people%20to%20ask%20about%20it%2C%20to%20keep%20the%20Holocaust%20in%20living%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Ron%E2%80%99s%20mind%2C%20this%20replicated%20number%20represents%20continuity.%20It%20ensures%20there%20are%20still%20people%20%E2%80%9Cwalking%20with%20the%20number%E2%80%9D.%20He%20says%20he%20wanted%20to%20experience%20what%20his%20father%20had%20experienced%20when%20his%20name%20was%20taken%20away.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20Rony%20Cohen%20says%20that%20deciding%20to%20replicate%20her%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20tattoo%20was%20so%20%E2%80%9Cshe%20could%20walk%20with%20me%20for%20good%20%E2%80%93%20it%E2%80%99s%20a%20statement%20for%20me%E2%80%9D.%20Cohen%20too%20wanted%20it%20in%20the%20same%20place%20as%20the%20original%2C%20so%20that%20everyone%20understood%20its%20meaning.%20She%20sees%20her%20body%20as%20becoming%20a%20conduit%20for%20her%20grandmother%20%E2%80%93%20a%20means%20to%20keep%20her%20legacy%20and%20life%20with%20her%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20contrast%20to%20Ron%2C%20though%2C%20Cohen%20did%20not%20broach%20the%20subject%20with%20her%20grandmother.%20She%20just%20went%20ahead%20and%20got%20the%20tattoo%2C%20then%20wore%20long%20sleeves%20at%20family%20gatherings%20%E2%80%93%20much%20like%20some%20survivors%20had%20in%20previous%20decades.%20But%20for%20her%2C%20covering%20the%20tattoo%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20because%20of%20stigma.%20Rather%2C%20she%20worried%20about%20the%20reactions%20it%20might%20trigger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20Cohen%20decided%20to%20show%20the%20number%20to%20her%20grandmother.%20She%20videoed%20her%20response.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20first%2C%20her%20grandmother%20asks%20why%20Cohen%20has%20done%20it.%20Then%20she%20asks%20if%20it%20hurt.%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20you%20to%20do%20something%20that%20hurts%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CNo%20it%20didn%E2%80%99t%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20replies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20which%20her%20grandmother%20asks%3A%20%E2%80%9CWhy%3F%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20is%20very%20clear%20that%20getting%20her%20tattoo%20was%20a%20personal%20act%2C%20a%20decision%20relating%20to%20her%20own%20history%2C%20not%20to%20a%20larger%20historical%20one.%20%E2%80%9CI%E2%80%99m%20not%20a%20monument%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%20%E2%80%9CI%20don%E2%80%99t%20carry%20the%20Jewish%20nation%20on%20my%20back.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20the%20Holocaust%20passes%20out%20of%20living%20memory%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMuseums%20and%20memorials%20all%20over%20the%20world%20are%20dedicated%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fwhy-we-still-need-to-teach-young-people-about-the-holocaust-90481%5C%22%3Etelling%20the%20story%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20Holocaust.%20Since%202006%2C%20International%20Holocaust%20Remembrance%20Day%20has%20been%20marked%20every%20year%20on%20January%2027.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20the%20proliferation%20of%20Holocaust-related%20art%20and%20culture%2C%20despite%20the%20books%20laying%20out%20the%20facts%2C%20research%20shows%20many%20people%20are%20ignorant%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pewresearch.org%2Freligion%2F2020%2F01%2F22%2Fwhat-americans-know-about-the-holocaust%2F%5C%22%3Ewhat%20happened%3C%2Fa%3E.%20In%202021%2C%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fwww.claimscon.org%2Fuk-study%2F%5C%22%3Eglobal%20Holocaust%20Awareness%3C%2Fa%3E%20Survey%20found%20large%20gaps%20in%20people%E2%80%99s%20knowledge.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20UK%2C%2052%25%20of%20respondents%20could%20not%20specify%20that%20six%20million%20Jewish%20people%20had%20been%20murdered%20%E2%80%93%20a%20number%20which%20rose%20to%2056%25%20in%20Austria%20and%2057%25%20in%20France.%20Of%20the%20adults%20surveyed%20in%20the%20US%20and%20Canada%2C%2045%25%20and%2049%25%2C%20respectively%2C%20were%20unable%20to%20name%20a%20concentration%20camp%20or%20a%20ghetto.%20Among%20millennials%20in%20the%20US%2C%20only%2049%25%20could%20name%20a%20concentration%20camp%20or%20ghetto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20matters%20because%2C%20as%20we%20reach%20the%2079th%20anniversary%20of%20the%20liberation%20of%20Auschwitz%20on%20January%2027%201945%2C%20there%20are%20very%20few%20survivors%20left%20to%20give%20a%20first-hand%20account%20of%20what%20was%20done%20to%20them.%20The%20Holocaust%20is%20passing%20out%20of%20living%20memory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20those%20whose%20family%20history%20is%20tied%20up%20with%20the%20Holocaust%2C%20memorialising%20it%20is%20both%20public%20and%20private.%20The%20tattoo%20replicating%20the%20Auschwitz%20number%20is%20a%20form%20of%20memorial%20practice%20that%20speaks%2C%20viscerally%2C%20to%20their%20own%20family%20history%20%E2%80%93%20but%20also%20to%20the%20imperative%20to%20never%20forget.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EI%20spoke%20with%20David%20Rubin%20in%20the%20summer%20of%202022.%20He%20bears%20his%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20number%20on%20his%20arm%2C%20the%20number%20depicted%20as%20if%20written%20on%20a%20piece%20of%20wood%20alongside%20a%20Star%20of%20David%2C%20a%20thorny%20vine%20of%20lilac-coloured%20flowers%20entwined%20around%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20of%20the%20flowers%20are%20open%2C%20representing%20his%20grandmother%2C%20Piroska%20%E2%80%9CPerl%E2%80%9D%20Levy%2C%20and%20her%20surviving%20sisters.%20To%20the%20left%20lie%20two%20closed%20flowers%2C%20for%20her%20two%20sisters%20who%20were%20killed.%20A%20lone%20flower%20completes%20the%20floral%20framing%20at%20the%20bottom%2C%20in%20memory%20of%20her%20brother%2C%20also%20killed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20Rubin%E2%80%99s%20mind%2C%20his%20generation%20is%20probably%20the%20last%20to%20speak%20about%20this.%20Getting%20the%20tattoo%20was%20a%20means%20of%20ensuring%20that%20the%20fourth%20generation%20%E2%80%93%20his%20children%2C%20his%20grandmother%E2%80%99s%20great-grandchildren%20%E2%80%93%20will%20know%20what%20happened.%20%E2%80%9CI%20wanted%20a%20story%2C%20instead%20of%20just%20a%20number%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%20The%20barbed%20wire%20has%20become%20the%20thorny%20vine%20in%20flower.%20%E2%80%9CIt%E2%80%99s%20taking%20the%20bad%20thing%20and%20%5Bre%5Dcreating%20it%20as%20a%20good%20thing.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMemorial%20tattoos%20are%20a%20way%20of%20expressing%20a%20life%20story.%20They%20are%20an%20external%20scar%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdoi.org%2F10.1080%2F07481187.2021.1983889%5C%22%3Eembodies%3C%2Fa%3E%20an%20internal%20one.%20The%20writer%20Eva%20Hoffman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.penguin.co.uk%2Fbooks%2F358115%2Fafter-such-knowledge-by-eva-hoffman%2F9780099464723%5C%22%3Enotes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20even%20where%20there%20are%20silences%20in%20how%20families%2C%20including%20her%20own%2C%20reckon%20with%20their%20traumatic%20past%2C%20the%20%E2%80%9Clanguage%20of%20the%20body%E2%80%9D%20still%20breaches%20those%20silences.%20It%20keeps%20the%20unspoken%20past%20ever%20present.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20descendants%20of%20Holocaust%20survivors%20did%20not%20experience%20the%20trauma%20directly%2C%20the%20intergenerational%20trauma%20is%20long-lasting.%20Rony%20Cohen%20was%20not%20the%20only%20grandchild%20of%20a%20survivor%20who%20told%20me%20they%20dream%20or%20have%20nightmares%20about%20the%20Holocaust.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20doing%20these%20interviews%2C%20I%20have%20found%20that%20replicating%20the%20Auschwitz%20tattoo%20is%20an%20expression%20of%20the%20love%20felt%20towards%20the%20survivor%20relative%2C%20and%20a%20way%20of%20keeping%20the%20memory%20of%20the%20Holocaust%20alive.%20It%20is%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthesociologicalreview.org%2Fpodcasts%2Fthe-stigma-conversations%2Ftattooing-and-resistance-with-alice-bloch%2F%5C%22%3Eact%20of%20reclaiming%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20painful%20family%20history.%20And%20for%20some%2C%20it%20is%20about%20connections%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Ffrom-the-manchester-bee-to-the-pompey-dot-the-psychology-of-regional-tattoos-198695%5C%22%3Eto%20a%20collective%20identity%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20way%2C%20it%20is%20about%20the%20future%20too.%20When%20there%20are%20no%20more%20survivors%20to%20share%20their%20stories%2C%20these%20descendants%20who%20bear%20on%20their%20living%20bodies%20the%20numbers%20once%20forcibly%20tattooed%20on%20their%20relatives%20will%20stand%20as%20a%20living%20reminder%20of%20where%20racism%20and%20hatred%20can%20lead.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Falice-bloch-1451307%5C%22%3EAlice%20Bloch%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Professor%20of%20Sociology%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Funiversity-of-manchester-1204%5C%22%3EUniversity%20of%20Manchester%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20is%20republished%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%5C%22%3EThe%20Conversation%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20a%20Creative%20Commons%20license.%20Read%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fdescendants-of-holocaust-survivors-explain-why-they-are-replicating-auschwitz-tattoos-on-their-own-bodies-206821%5C%22%3Eoriginal%20article%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706524229000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F29152947%2FScreenshot-2024-01-29-at-3.27.08-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fdescendants-of-holocaust-survivors-are-replicating-auschwitz-tattoos-on-their-own-bodies%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20the%20Holocaust%20passes%20out%20of%20living%20memory%2C%20replicating%20an%20Auschwitz%20tattoo%20becomes%20an%20ever%20more%20potent%20gesture%20about%20embodied%20memorialisation%20and%2C%20crucially%2C%20familial%20ties%20and%20love.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fhistory%2Fdescendants-of-holocaust-survivors-are-replicating-auschwitz-tattoos-on-their-own-bodies%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22This%20Election%20Season%2C%20Who%20Gets%20to%20Take%20the%20Credit%20for%20Jobs%20and%20Reservation%20in%20Bihar%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F05184147%2FFxHyj_3aEAMGYQ6.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20has%20taken%20away%20Nitish%20Kumar%20from%20the%20Indian%20National%20Developmental%20Inclusive%20Alliance%20is%20for%20all%20to%20see.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20this%20election%20season%2C%20will%20the%20Nitish-led%20National%20Democratic%20Alliance%20(NDA)%20government%20in%20Bihar%20be%20able%20to%20take%20away%20the%20credit%20for%20giving%20four%20lakh%20jobs%20and%20hiking%20the%20quota%20for%20the%20marginalised%20classes%20up%20to%2065%25%20from%20the%20Rashtriya%20Janata%20Dal%20and%20its%20leader%2C%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EVeteran%20socialist%20leader%20and%20RJD%20national%20vice-president%20Shivanand%20Tivary%20said%20it%20will%20be%20impossible%20for%20Nitish%20Kumar%20and%20the%20BJP%20to%20spin%20these%20as%20successes%20of%20just%20Nitish%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20caste-survey%2C%20the%20raising%20of%20reservation%20to%2065%25%20and%20giving%20jobs%20on%20a%20huge%20scale%20are%20part%20of%20the%20larger%20cause%20of%20social%20justice%20that%20is%20central%20to%20RJD%E2%80%99s%20politics.%20Nitish%20was%20compelled%20to%20do%20it%20by%20Tejashwi%2C%20who%20had%20promised%20the%20same%20in%20the%202020%20assembly%20elections%2C%E2%80%9D%20Tivary%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETejashwi%2C%20who%20has%20now%20lost%20his%20position%20as%20the%20deputy%20chief%20minister%2C%20had%20explicitly%20promised%20to%20give%2010%20lakh%20jobs%20in%20the%20event%20of%20coming%20to%20power%20in%202020%20assembly%20polls.%20His%20promise%20clicked.%20The%20RJD%20emerging%20as%20the%20single%20largest%20party%2C%20with%2079%20MLAs.%20Nitish%20whose%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20was%20reduced%20to%2045%20seats%20in%20those%20polls%20had%20purportedly%20wondered%20in%20close%20circles%20as%20to%20where%20Tejashwi%20thought%20he%20would%20get%20the%20money%20to%20deliver%20this%20promise.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20dumped%20the%20BJP%20and%20shifted%20to%20the%20RJD-Congress-Left%20alliance%20on%20August%209%2C%202022.%20In%20his%20Independence%20Day%20address%20on%20August%2015%2C%202022%2C%20Nitish%20announced%20that%20he%20would%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20implement%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20promise.%20By%20then%20Tejashwi%20had%20become%20his%20deputy%20and%20was%20present%20at%20the%20event.%20The%20chief%20minister%20promised%20%3Cem%3Emore%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Ethan%3C%2Fem%3E%2010%20lakh%20jobs.%20He%20distributed%202.20%20lakh%20appointment%20letters%20to%20teachers%20in%20an%20unparalleled%20spectacle%20at%20Patna%E2%80%99s%20Gandhi%20Maidan%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20education%20department%20which%20was%20understood%20to%20be%20under%20the%20RJD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20flight%20of%20Nitish%20to%20the%20BJP%20on%20Sunday%2C%20January%2028%2C%20was%20preceded%20by%20an%20advertisement%20war%20on%20the%20credit%20for%20development%20in%20Bihar.%20Tejashwi%E2%80%99s%20image%20had%20notably%20been%20missing%20on%20the%20state%20government%E2%80%99s%20advertisements%2C%20which%20had%20carried%20the%20picture%20of%20the%20CM%20alone.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20irked%20RJD%20cadres%20who%20displayed%20pictures%20of%20Tejashwi%20with%20a%20list%20of%20his%20achievements%20at%20the%20RJD%20headquarters%20in%20retaliation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fayaram-gayaram-politics-of-nitish-at-play-poised-to-rejoin-nda%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fayaram-gayaram-politics-of-nitish-at-play-poised-to-rejoin-nda%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EAyaram%20Gayaram%20Politics%20of%20Nitish%20at%20Play%2C%20Poised%20to%20Rejoin%20NDA%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20the%20BJP-JD(U)%E2%80%99s%20strategists%20were%20at%20work%20to%20take%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%20Nitish%20%E2%80%93%20the%20credit%20for%20giving%20jobs%20became%20evident%20when%20the%20CM%20in%20his%20first%20statement%20after%20switching%20sides%20to%20the%20BJP%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20was%20working%20hard%20for%20Bihar%20and%20they%20%5Bwithout%20naming%20RJD%5D%20were%20interested%20in%20taking%20credit%20alone.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20response%2C%20Tejashwi%20said%20that%20the%20CM%20had%20a%20problem%20with%20RJD%20getting%20the%20credit%20for%20its%20achievements.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20were%20the%20largest%20component%20of%20the%20grand%20alliance%20government.%20We%20had%20education%2C%20health%2C%20tourism%2C%20sports%20and%20other%20key%20departments%20in%20our%20quota.%20The%20RJD%20ministers%20worked%20hard%20to%20fulfil%20our%20promises%20to%20the%20people.%20How%20could%20we%20be%20denied%20the%20credit%20for%20our%20work%3F%E2%80%9D%20he%20told%20reporters.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESocial%20justice%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhatever%20the%20BJP%20claims%2C%20it%20is%20a%20fact%20that%20the%20Hindutva%20party%20was%20feeling%20hugely%20insecure%20in%20Bihar%20with%20Nitish%20Kumar%20on%20the%20alliance%E2%80%99s%20side.%20Bihar%20under%20the%20alliance%20had%20produced%20what%20looked%20like%20a%20potent%20counter-narrative%20with%20the%20centrality%20of%20social%20justice%20in%20its%20operations.%20It%20appeared%20to%20make%20good%20on%20the%20promise%20%E2%80%93%20%3Cem%3Ejiski%20jitni%20bhagidari%2C%20uski%20utni%20hissedari%3C%2Fem%3E%20or%20proportionate%20representation%20to%20the%20marginalised%20classes%20in%20governance%20apparatus.%20Issues%20of%20disparity%2C%20deprivation%2C%20livelihood%2C%20health%20and%20sustenance%20concerning%20the%20common%20people%20took%20prominence%20against%20Hindutva%20politics%20which%20aggressively%20pursued%20religious%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECreating%20buzz%20in%20the%20name%20of%20the%20Hindu%20deity%20Ram%2C%20the%20BJP%20was%20confident%20that%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20juggernaut%20would%20sail%20through%20smoothly%20in%20Uttar%20Pradesh%2C%20Rajasthan%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Chhattisgarh.%20But%20that%20it%20might%20be%20stuck%20in%20Bihar%20%E2%80%93%20where%20with%20Nitish%20BJP%20had%20bagged%2039%20seats%20out%20of%2040%20in%20the%202019%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20was%20not%20lost%20on%20them.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20core%20of%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cinsecurity%E2%80%9D%20was%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20and%20RJD%E2%80%99s%20proven%20track%20record%20as%20a%20champion%20of%20social%20justice.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20novelty%20of%20Tejashwi%20was%20he%20had%20added%20economic%20justice%20%E2%80%93%20emphasising%20on%20jobs%2C%20sports%2C%20tourism%2C%20IT%20and%20investment%20%E2%80%93%20to%20expanding%20on%20his%20father%E2%80%99s%20battle%20for%20social%20justice%20and%20attracting%20youths%20to%20his%20party.%20Much%20ahead%20of%20Nitish%E2%80%99s%20entry%20into%20the%20alliance%2C%20the%20RJD%20under%20the%20stewardship%20of%20Tejashwi%20was%20demanding%20caste%20surveys%2C%20raising%20the%20quota%20for%20the%20backward%20classes%2C%20Scheduled%20Castes%20and%20Scheduled%20Tribes%2C%20while%20at%20once%20launching%20a%20frontal%20attack%20on%20the%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20on%20the%20issues%20of%20radical%20Hindutva%2C%20the%20subverting%20constitution%2C%20subjugating%20democratic%20institutions%20and%20misusing%20investigating%20agencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%C2%A0%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwith-job-mahakumbha-nitish-kumar-foregrounds-importance-of-promises-kept%5C%22%20data-stringify-link%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwith-job-mahakumbha-nitish-kumar-foregrounds-importance-of-promises-kept%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%20data-sk%3D%5C%22tooltip_parent%5C%22%3EWith%20Job%20%E2%80%98Mahakumbha%E2%80%99%2C%20Nitish%20Kumar%20Foregrounds%20Importance%20of%20Promises%20Kept%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOstensibly%2C%20Nitish%20carrying%20the%20socialist%20legacy%20was%20favourable%20to%20the%20social%20justice%20plank.%20But%20he%20was%20able%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20caste%20survey%2C%20raise%20the%20reservation%20limit%20up%20to%2065%25%20and%20give%20employment%20on%20a%20huge%20scale%20to%20the%20youths%20only%20after%20he%20joined%20the%20alliance.%20In%20fact%2C%20the%20demand%20for%20the%20Caste%20Census%20at%20the%20national%20level%20became%20the%20basis%20for%20the%20JDU-RJD%20alliance%20with%20Nitish%20and%20Tejashwi%20forwarding%20this%20demand%20to%20the%20Union%20government.%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20government%20opposed%20the%20caste%20survey%20in%20Bihar%20in%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%20subsequently.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Bihar%20caste%20survey%20and%20reservation%20limit%20raise%20provided%20the%20first%20potent%20template%20for%20the%20INDIA%20bloc%20to%20counter%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20Hindutva%20drive.%20In%20fact%2C%20Rahul%20Gandhi%2C%20despite%20the%20veiled%20objections%20from%20his%20party%E2%80%99s%20old%20guards%2C%20adopted%20the%20Bihar%20%E2%80%98model%E2%80%99%20and%20promised%20the%20Caste%20Census%20in%20his%20campaigns%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20Chhattisgarh%20and%20Rajasthan.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20course%2C%20the%20BJP%20won%20these%20three%20states%20in%20the%20recent%20assembly%20polls%20and%20tried%20to%20create%20the%20perception%20that%20Hindutva%20politics%20had%20defeated%20%E2%80%9Ccaste%20politics%E2%80%9D.%20But%20the%20fact%20remains%20that%20the%20Congress%20upped%20or%20retained%20its%20vote-percentage%20as%20it%20lost%20marginally%20in%20terms%20of%20votes%2C%20if%20not%20in%20terms%20of%20seats%2C%20to%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EBharat%20Ratna%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20despite%20putting%20up%20a%20brave%20face%2C%20the%20Hindutva%20party%20was%2C%20apparently%2C%20in%20the%20grip%20of%20fear%20about%20the%20social%20justice%20plank%2C%20at%20least%2C%20in%20Bihar%20which%20had%20Lalu%20Prasad%20Yadav%20holding%20on%20to%20his%20strength%20with%20the%20backward%20classes%20and%20minorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELalu%20had%20decisively%20defeated%20the%20BJP%20in%20all%20elections%20%E2%80%93%20assembly%20and%20Lok%20Sabha%20%E2%80%93%20from%201991%20to%202004%20when%20the%20Hindutva%20party%20under%20L.K%20Advani%20and%20A.B%20Vajpayee%20had%20made%20reasonable%20inroads%20in%20other%20states%20of%20the%20Hindi%20heartland%2C%20including%20Uttar%20Pradesh.%20And%20despite%20his%20party%20losing%20power%20to%20Nitish%20with%20the%20BJP%20in%202005%2C%20Lalu%E2%80%99s%20RJD%20stayed%20strong%20with%20its%20support%20of%20the%20backward%20classes%20including%20the%20Yadavs%20who%20are%20the%20single%20largest%20backward%20caste%20and%20the%20minorities%20at%20the%20grassroots%20level%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%20had%20symbolic%20as%20well%20as%20substantive%20reasons%20to%20fear%20the%20prospect%20of%20Lalu%20united%20with%20Nitish.%20Even%20if%20Nitish%20was%20reduced%20to%2015%25%20vote-share%20in%202014%20Lok%20Sabha%20polls%2C%20his%20presence%20in%20the%20alliance%20could%20have%20been%20the%20%E2%80%9Cplus%E2%80%9D%20factor%20to%20the%20alliance%20in%20Bihar.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20was%20calculating%20all%20these%20factors%20that%20the%20Bharat%20Ratna%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20conferred%20upon%20Karpoori%20Thakur%20%E2%80%93%20the%20father%20of%20the%20social%20justice%20movement%20%E2%80%93%20posthumously%2C%20a%20day%20after%20Narendra%20Modi%20consecrated%20the%20Ram%20temple%20at%20Ayodhya.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENotably%2C%20Nitish%20had%20thanked%20the%20PM%20for%20the%20same%20in%20his%20address%20at%20the%20event%20to%20celebrate%20Karpoori%20Thakur%E2%80%99s%20100th%20anniversary%20at%20Patna%E2%80%99s%20Gandhi%20Maidan%20on%20January%2024.%20He%20also%20attacked%20the%20%E2%80%9Cpromotion%20of%20sons%20and%20daughters%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20without%20naming%20the%20RJD.%20He%20said%20that%20like%20Karpoori%20Thakur%20he%20too%20had%20not%20promoted%20his%20family%20members%20in%20politics.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENitish%20has%20now%20replaced%20Lalu%E2%80%99s%20son%20with%20Samrat%20Choudhary%2C%20son%20of%20the%20famous%20Koiri%20leader%20of%20his%20time%20and%20former%20minister%20Shakuni%20Choudhary%2C%20as%20his%20deputy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20has%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9C%3Cem%3EKhela%20ab%20shuru%20hua%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%9C.%20The%20game%20has%20begun%20now.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ENalin%20Verma%20is%20a%20senior%20journalist%2C%20author%2C%20media%20educator%2C%20and%20independent%20researcher%20in%20folklore.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706522867000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2F05184147%2FFxHyj_3aEAMGYQ6.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthis-election-season-who-gets-to-take-the-credit-for-jobs-and-reservation-in-bihar%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Nitish%20Kumar%20and%20his%20former%20deputy%20Tejashwi%20Yadav%20are%20now%20locked%20in%20a%20tussle%20over%20who%20is%20responsible%20for%20their%20government's%20noteworthy%20actions.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A10%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fthis-election-season-who-gets-to-take-the-credit-for-jobs-and-reservation-in-bihar%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Wildlife%20charity%20with%20Harry%20as%20board%20member%20investigating%20rape%20allegations%20against%20eco-guards%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706521140000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-prince-harry-duke-of-sussex_6436758.jpg%3F20240129094911%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fafrican-wildlife-charity-with-prince-harry-as-board-member-investigating-rape-and-torture-claims-against-eco-guards-13059259%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20wildlife%20charity%20which%20has%20Prince%20Harry%20as%20a%20board%20member%20is%20investigating%20allegations%20of%20human%20rights%20abuses%20by%20its%20guards%20in%20the%20Republic%20of%20the%20Congo.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A91%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fafrican-wildlife-charity-with-prince-harry-as-board-member-investigating-rape-and-torture-claims-against-eco-guards-13